Package core

Interface HlaPhysicalEntityManager

  • public interface HlaPhysicalEntityManager
    Manager used to manage HlaPhysicalEntitys.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener

        void addHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaPhysicalEntityListener listener)
        Add a listener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaPhysicalEntity (Both local and remote). The listener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaPhysicalEntity is updated. The listener is also called when an interaction is sent to an instance of HlaPhysicalEntity. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener

        void removeHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaPhysicalEntityListener listener)
        Remove a listener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaPhysicalEntity. Note: The listener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaPhysicalEntity. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void addHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaPhysicalEntityValueListener valueListener)
        Add a valueListener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaPhysicalEntity (Both local and remote). The Valuelistener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaPhysicalEntity is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void removeHlaPhysicalEntityDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaPhysicalEntityValueListener valueListener)
        Remove a valueListener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaPhysicalEntity. Note: The valueListener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaPhysicalEntity. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the HlaPhysicalEntity manager. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaPhysicalEntity manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable the HlaPhysicalEntity manager, otherwise false

      • setEnabledIfAvailableInFom

        void setEnabledIfAvailableInFom()
        Enables the HlaPhysicalEntity manager if it is available in the FOM at runtime. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaPhysicalEntity manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Check if the HlaPhysicalEntity manager is actually enabled when connected. An HlaPhysicalEntity manager may be disabled with the setEnabled(false) function, or it may be configured as if available in the FOM by the setEnabledIfAvailableInFom() function and then not available in the FOM at runtime.

        This method should only be used when connected, it will always return false when not connected.

        Returns:
        true if connected and the HlaPhysicalEntity manager is enabled.
